      "content": "I hear you, and it sounds truly overwhelming. Feeling like there's no \"us to turn to\" or strength left can make everything seem even harder. But please know that it's okay to have these thoughts, and expressing them is a crucial part of healing. People often can't see what you're going through, but a small gesture can sometimes mean the world. You don't have to face this alone. There are people who care, who want to help you, even if they don't always know how. I'm here for you to talk, to share these thoughts, or even just to be there with you. Loss and grief are deeply personal and different for everyone. If you ever consider reaching out, I'm here, or we could even look for a professional who can offer a different perspective. You're not alone, even when you might not feel that way. Taking a small step towards finding support can sometimes light a path to healing and give you the strength to continue, though I understand that might not feel possible right now.",
